Notes:
OLD PORT direct to 43 North (call on VHF 9 for dock, expect near restaurant, ok to sit on dock during lunch).  Lunch at 43 North then out to headlight and back to OLD PORT.  Must be back to OLD PORT at 2:30 for flight out.

Details

12:15pm - Pick up at the Public Water Taxi Dock in the Old Port. 

12:30pm - Arrive at 43 North (we will plan on just cruising directly there)

12:30 - 1:30 pm - Lunch at 43 North

1:30pm - Depart 43 North aboard our charter vessel

1:30 - 2:30pm - Sightseeing Cruise (See attached map for route.  We should be able to get out to Portland Head Light and back)

2:30pm - drop off at Public Water Taxi Dock in Old Port

Activity / Add-On: Private Sunset Dinner Cruise with Chef Paul Lively
Tickets / Items: 1x 3-hr Private Dinner Charter (price is for dinner for 2). Add additional guests on next screen
Notes:
Email is nancy.anaseth@gmail.com

6:30pm--Depart from our private dock at South Port Marine, 14 Ocean St, South Portland, Maine.

Your family will then depart Portland Harbor and do brief amount of sightseeing before dropping anchor at a good fireworks viewing spot around 7:45. During the sightseeing cruise and while awaiting the fireworks show, Chef Paul Olaf Lively will prepare and serve you a fantastic 4th of July feast featuring fresh local ingredients and Maine seafood.

Approx 9:15pm--Fireworks display followed by the dessert course.

10:30 PM--M/V MONHEGAN will return to your departure point.
Activity: Private Sunset Dinner Cruise with Chef Paul Lively

Activity / Add-On: Sightseeing Charter with Island Dining Excursion aboard the MARIE L
Tickets / Items: 1x Private Charter for up to 20 guests
Notes:
Wedding cruise for 12-14
4:00pm--Depart from Portland's Old Port.
We will cruise past some of Portland's best coastal sights including lighthouses and historic stone fortresses and then stop in a scenic spot for your wedding ceremony. 
The ceremony will take place aboard MARIE L, and after it concludes, we will make our way to the Crown Jewel on Great Diamond Island for some celebration. 
GUESTS NEED TO ARRIVE AT CROWN JEWEL AT 5:45. Drinks on the patio and dinner at Crown Jewel. 
8:00ish--reboard MARIE L for the return trip to South Portland as the sun sets.
9:00pm--MARIE L will return to your departure point.
Additional Information
This charter is a private charter, meaning only your group is aboard along with your captain and tour guide. We do not have a wedding officiant on staff, so please plan accordingly for your ceremony

Activity / Add-On: Private Charter aboard MONHEGAN with South Portland departure
Notes:
WILL PAY CASH AT TIME OF CHARTER or owe $1600 on credit card. Cancellation policy reviewed and card on file.  Party of 4.  Oyster Farm tour plus 4 x lobster rolls/lunch/snacks from Paul.  See itinerary below: 

Price breakdown:  $300 to CIO; $275 to Paul: 

10:00 AM Departure from Portland - We will go directly to Chebeague Island Oyster Co

11:45 AM Arrive at the Oyster Farm and meet the owner and see how they raise oysters.  Sample Fresh oysters right from Casco Bay!

12:30 PM - Depart from the oyster farm and go to Jewell Island, enjoying lobster rolls from our chef along the way.  

1:45 PM - Arrive at Jewell Island.  There is no dock at Jewell, but we will anchor is a sheltered cove and row ashore.  Once on Jewell (an uninhabited island), you can explore the hiking trails and climb in the WW-II era lookout towers for great views of Casco Bay.  

3:30 PM - Depart Jewell Island and return to Portland by way of Ram Island Light, Portland Head Light, Fort Scammel, House Island, Spring Point Light, Bug Light and some of the other historic sights in the Portland area.  

5:00 PM - Arrive back in Portland.

Notes:
OLD PORT Pickup - group of 6 adults for sightseeing and stop at Peaks.  May have lunch at Peaks.  Cockeyed Gull is OPEN at 11:30.  they don't take lunch reservations but said should be no problem getting a table. 



Here is a summary of your itinerary:
19:00am--Depart from the Portland Public Water Taxi Dock at 72 Commercial St, Portland, ME 04101.

Your group will then enjoy about 2-hours of sightseeing featuring the best coastal sights in the Portland area including historic stone forts, wildlife, and lighthouses.

Approx 11:00am--Your group will go ashore at Peaks Island and have lunch at either Cockeyed Gull or Inn on Peaks. (We will check availability for you and update you on options).

An alternative option is to order food from our Chef to enjoy on board and then spend some time exploring Peaks Island.

This charter is a private charter, meaning only your group is aboard along with your captain and tour guide.

12:45pm--You will reboard M/V MONHEGAN and return to Portland.

See below for idea on how we can help with engagement: 

For the big question, I'm thinking about having her do a Titanic type pose where she is looking out the back of the boat and then I will get on my knee behind her and have her turn around then ask the big question.  I'm thinking if we can coordinate this with the Captain or Chef and he/she can say something along the lines that it's a tradition on the boat to do a Titanic pose at sunset (or whenever/wherever you would think is best) on the boat then coordinate her to looking straight out the back of the boat and I will ask the big question?  Also, they can take my phone too acting like we are about to take a photo to capture the special moment on video. What do you think about that?  Possibly once we get to a certain location or it turns sunset then he can come out and tell us that it's time for that Titanic pose (preferably an hour plus in to the boat ride).

Itinerary text: 

Hi Joe-

We have created your reservation for a private charter aboard the historic MARIE L! 

#**Here is a summary of your itinerary:**

**3:00pm**--Depart from the Portland Public Water Taxi Dock in Portlands Old Port at **72 Commercial St, Portland, Maine.**

Once aboard, relax with your friends and family and enjoy our selection of local beers, imported wines, and other drinks as we cruise past some of Portland's best coastal sights.  We'll stop in a calm, scenic spot for an intimate, on-board wedding ceremony, officiated by your Captain.

There'll be time for some celebration and enjoyment of any food or cake you'd like to bring aboard.  We'll keep the drinks flowing as we continue to cruise Casco Bay, **returning to Portland around 6pm**.

This is a private charter so only your group will be on board along with a captain and deckhand.


#**Additional Information**

The cost for this charter is $115/person plus applicable taxes).  This rate includes all drinks (champagne, wine, beer, spiked seltzers, and non-alcoholic drinks) and also includes the services of your Captain as officiant.  **A $300 deposit is due within 7 days to secure your reservation**, with balance due prior to your charter departure.  The balance will be applied to your card on file prior to your departure unless you make alternative payment arrangements with us. 
  
You can pay your deposit by filling in the contact and payment information in the fields below.  Upon receipt of payment, you will receive a confirmation email that contains the address of your departure point and other important details.  **Reservations are not guaranteed until the deposit is received. **

We do have onboard catering available.  Please call or visit our website for details. Alternatively, you are welcome to bring your own food onboard if desired. Please be sure to bring appropriate cups, plates, napkins, utensils, etc.  

If the unexpected occurs and you need to cancel, we will gladly offer a full refund if you can provide appropriate documentation of your circumstances.  Similarly, if we determine that weather conditions are not conducive to a great experience on the water, we will offer you the option of rebooking or a full refund.  More information about our cancellation policy can be found on our website, cascobaycustomcharters.com

Notes:
wedding transportation - OLD PORT pick up @ 2pm direct transportation to TEIA - group of 16 wedding party

$400 total 

FROM TEIA 

"The only thing that you need to cover with them is that TEIA only has a little over 4 feet of water at the dock float at dead low tide and they cannot throw their docking lines around TEIA's wooden cleats and use their engine power to pull their boat into the dock. Our cleats are for tying up pleasure boats - large heavy power boats using their engines to pull their boat into the dock using their dock lines around the TEIA cleats can tear the cleats off the deck. They need to ease their boat up to dockside and stop the boat before engaging their dock lines to the dock bolsters not the cleats. Boats that draw more than 4 feet could not come into the TEIA dock at dead low tide"
